[recto] Ad [Addendum] 39? [sic] Bruegel. B.M. [British Museum] Printroom. [A.E.] Popham 12 [= Catalogue of drawings by Dutch and Flemish artists preserved in the department of prints and drawings in the British Museum, V: V : Dutch and Flemish drawings of the XV and XVI centuries, London: British Museum, 1932], p. 146, N° 12, Pl. XLVII]; Copy: Dances at Village Festival repr. by Hollar; The drawing repr. in cat. pl. XLVII, but chalk parts (e.g. bride at table) not visible in reproduction. Important note by Popham. This drawing to be taken into consideration of Wedding problem; [verso] Look up Bisschop.
